  "response": "The answer to the riddle is **\"memory.\"**\n\nHere's how it fits:\n\n1. **\"You will always find me in the past.\"**\n   - Memories are recollections of past events, so they inherently belong to the past.\n\n2. **\"I can be created in the present.\"**\n   - As you experience new moments, you form new memories.\n\nThus, \"memory\" perfectly aligns with both parts of the riddle.",
